      %li	We can create applications that offer similar features and services to, or otherwise compete with, your application.

  %li Amendments 
  %ul 
    %li We can change this Statement if we provide you notice (by posting the change on the GTB Governance Page) and an opportunity to comment.  To get notice of any future changes to this Statement, visit our GTB Governance Page and become a fan.
    %li	For changes to sections 7, 8, 9, and 11 (sections relating to payments, application developers, website operators, and advertisers), we will give you a minimum of three days notice. For all other changes we will give you a minimum of seven days notice. All such comments must be made on the GTB Governance Page
    %li	If more than 5,000 users comment on the proposed change, we will also give you the opportunity to participate in a vote in which you will be provided alternatives. The vote shall be binding on us if more than 30% of all active registered users as of the date of the notice vote.
    %li	We can make changes for legal or administrative reasons, or to correct an inaccurate statement, upon notice without opportunity to comment.
  %li Termination   
  %p 
    If you violate the letter or spirit of this Statement, or otherwise create risk or possible legal exposure for us, we can stop providing all or part of GTB to you. We will notify you by email or at the next time you attempt to access your account. You may also delete your account or disable your application at any time. In all such cases, this Statement shall terminate, but the following provisions will still apply: 2.2, 2.4, 3-5, 8.2, 9.1-9.3, 9.9, 9.10, 9.13, 9.15, 9.18, 10.3, 11.2, 11.5, 11.6, 11.9, 11.12, 11.13, and 14-18.

